<br>
Background is a regular is frustrated because her brother's LDS girlfriend was forced to dump him because of his atheism. My response was basically that prohibition on dating atheists or even non-sect theists is NOT unusual and should not lead anyone to be surprised and that indeed--<br>
<br>
&quot;teaching children intolerance based on belief systems is EXACTLY what religion (xianity in particular) is all about so you shouldn't be surprised&quot;<br>
<br>
We have touched on the intolerance of xianity many times here, but I see the teaching of this to children and enforcement of religious guidelines/proscriptions as the core issue. <br>
For the record I believe in religious liberty and do think theists have the same rights to teach their children as they believe...so is this guy wrong for forbidding his LDS daughter (at age 15 just a few short years from entering her sacred marriage and beginning the breeding process on her way to a heavenly family on planet ruled by priestly dh) to date non LDS? NO--he's just living his religion and making his kids do the same and she can reject this later in life. He as every right to embrace an intolerant, bigoted mythology and pass this off as truth to his children, so let's stay away from whether he has a right to indoctrinate his offspring--clearly he does as we all do. The core issue, as I've said is whether xianity breeds intolerance and whether teaching it to children = teaching religious based intolerance.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
ST<br>
