<br>
We've brought up the subject of tax exemptions for churches before, and there are also several humanist and freethinking organizations that have applied for and received that same tax-exempt status.  As for the Faith-Based Initiative and other crap being concocted by our Fundie-in-Chief--yes, it sucks, but the only way to eliminate this kind of discrimination is to work within the system--write to representatives, support candidates who share your views on this, be vocal in your community.  Public schools will only get away with school prayer if no one speaks up (and puts in a call to the ACLU).  We're not going to change the Xian faith (though personally I believe it's slowly on its way out), so we can forget about that.  A/A's need better organization and more publicity if they want to counter-attack the fundie right movement.  Teaming up with moderate-to-liberal Jewish and Xian groups who also carry the SOCAS banner and oppose institutionalized discrimination wouldn't be such a bad idea either.  (Wait, I think I just described the UUA  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ).<br>
