<br>
EVERYTHING Jesus Christ taught was about loving your neighbor, praying for those who are consciously trying to hurt you, not judging (that is God's alone) visiting the sick, taking care of the widows. Forgiving those who have offended you.  I dont see how any of that can be misconstrued as being intolerant.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, while not being intolerant of individuals, we do judge actions and behaviors and right and wrong and have the responsibility to speak out against things that we see as corrupting society as a whole.  If we were to be tolerant of EVERY behavior, we would have to just &quot;accept&quot;  thieves, rapists, people who assault others, pedophiles etc.  Are we Intolerant because we see these as problem behaviors? No.<br>
<br>
There are some things that we do not accept as OK behaviors, even if the rest of the world does.  Does that make us intolerant? Of the behavior or action, yes.  But that should NOT affect the way we interact or treat others on an individual basis.  <br>
<br>
A good example... Smoking.  I dont like it.  I think its a gross habit and addictive. I also know that every person has a right to choose whether or not to smoke.  I shouldnt treat a person badly because he chooses to smoke.  My grandma smoked all her life.  I didnt like it, but it didnt make me love her any less.  I didnt avoid visiting her because she smoked. But that doesnt mean I can't  be vocal about smoking laws and lobby to get no smoking in public places. <br>
<br>
I think there are things that every person feels passionately about.  Things that we disgree with other people about.  We can even get involved and try to make sure our voice is heard.  Whether it is the issue of Gay marriage or saving the rain forrest.   That does not mean on an individual basis we can't have a respectful pleasant relationship with the person with whom we disagree. - Shirene <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#EFEFEF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=monynh>monyNH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(8/13/03 9:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=240.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I think we're still missing the core issue </span><hr size=1> You'll have to excuse me for hogging the board tonight--I obviously have nothing better to do (yeah, right <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).<br>
