<br>
As to whether I think Christianity teaches intolerance in general...In my experience, I don't think so. I would say that intolerant people teach intolerance. And while there are intolerant people who are Christian, there are intolerant people who are Muslim, Jewish, Atheist and what have you as well. <br>
<br>
Your definitions were:<br>
Main Entry: in·tol·er·ant <br>
Pronunciation: -r&amp;nt<br>
Function: adjective<br>
Date: circa 1735<br>
1 : unable or unwilling to endure<br>
2 a : unwilling to grant equal freedom of expression especially in religious matters b : unwilling to grant or share social, political, or professional rights : BIGOTED<br>
- in·tol·er·ant·ly adverb<br>
- in·tol·er·ant·ness noun <br>
<br>
Main Entry: big·ot <br>
Pronunciation: 'bi-g&amp;t<br>
Function: noun<br>
Etymology: Middle French, hypocrite, bigot<br>
Date: 1661<br>
: a person obstinately or intolerantly devoted to his or her own opinions and prejudices<br>
<br>
And I do not think my upbringing (very Christian) taught those things at all. My parents are highly liberal &quot;social justice&quot; Catholics, if any of you are familiar with that term, and I think they used the phrase &quot;What would Jesus do?&quot; before it gained such popularity. My brothers and I heard that phrase often growing up when we had a question about how to behave and it was always used to mean, &quot;Is that the way you should treat another person?&quot;<br>
<br>
It is that upbringing and my Christian values that stem from it that make me anti-death penalty, pro-SOCAS, makes me despise racism, sexism and homophobia. Your definitions of intolerance &quot;unable or unwilling to endure&quot; and &quot;unwilling to grant equal freedom of expression especially in religious matters&quot; and &quot;unwilling to grant or share social, political, or professional rights&quot; are completely opposite how I was raised.<br>
<br>
Are there things in society I disagree with? You bet. Pornography is a good example...I think it is disgusting and degrading, especially to women, BUT as someone who wholeheartedly believes in SOCAS and the first amendment, I know that people have a right to create it and look at it. And I have the right to say it is disgusting and degrading. I don't think being tolerant means that I have to like everything I see, just that I cannot infringe on someone else's right to live their life.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I realize my experience is anecdotal only, but I do think it is an example of Christian parents who did not teach intolerance...because as I said, I believe intolerant people teach intolerance...be they Christian or not.<br>
<br>
Kerrie-Anne<br>
