<br>
New testament 1st Corinthians 11: 11<br>
- Neither is the man without the woman, neither the woman without the man, in the Lord.  <br>
<br>
1st Corinthians 7:2 Nevertheless, to avoid fornication, let <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>every man have his own wife</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and let <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>every woman have her own husband</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.... verses 8-9 I say therefore to the unmarried and the widows, it is good for them if they abide even as I, but if they cannot contain, let them marry: for it is better to marry than to burn.<br>
<br>
See they want the loophole of calling the un-natural union a marriage, so it won't be a sin.  You can't do that.<br>
<br>
I understand that you dont get it, but a priest should.  He knows the scriptures, He understands that the only person who can change &quot;god's rules&quot; is God.  So despite personal feelings, the rules are the rules.  My dh loves BEER.  If it were up to him beer would be the exception to the word of wisdom.  But it isnt up to him, It is God's law.  So he can either choose to follow it or not, but he can't just change the rules to suit his personal preference.<br>
<br>
Sex only in a marriage between a man and a woman is God's law.  Choose to live it or dont, but don't try to change God's law based on personal desires and still call it his law.  It the priest changed the law it would be &quot;Priest Bob&quot; 's law, not God's.<br>
<br>
I already stated that if they want to create a new catagory, a new type of homosexual legal commitment, go right ahead, just dont call it marriage. <br>
<br>
How did this thread turn into another debate on homosexuality?<br>
<br>
Please read the new testament and show me where it teaches intolerance.  <br>
<br>
No one addressed the idea of smoking and not treating a smoker differently because he smokes and yet still being vocal about smoking laws.  DO you agree? disagree? you dont want to comment because it might undermine your position that we (Christians) are intolerant and hate people because we speak out on political or public issues that we feel strongly about.  One doesnt equal the other.<br>
<br>
